comments: Anderson (MEM) maintains a legal guarding position and cleanly blocks Thompson's (GSW) shot during the play at the basket.
Anderson (MEM) cleanly blocks the shot and is the last player to touch the ball before it goes out of bounds. Possession correctly remains with Golden State.
Anderson (MEM) establishes his right foot as his pivot foot after securing the rebound, and then he lifts and returns it to the floor before releasing the pass.
Thompson (GSW) makes clean ball contact to dislodge it from Brooks (MEM) during the driving shot attempt.
Anderson (MEM) cleanly deflects Wiggins' (GSW) pass out of bounds. Possession correctly remains with Golden State.
Bane (MEM) extends his hand to Poole's (GSW) front, which affects his SQBR at the start of the drive.
Brooks (MEM) slides his pivot foot at the start of his dribble.
Brooks (MEM) moves laterally into Curry's (GSW) path and makes contact with his body, which affects his driving shot attempt.

Prior to receiving the pass, Green (GSW) and Jackson Jr. (MEM) engage and disengage as they attempt to establish position.  Green places an arm at Jackson Jr.'s side but does not dislodge him or impede his progress.
Green (GSW) maintains a legal guarding position during the driving shot attempt by Jackson Jr. (MEM).
Bane (MEM) extends his hands into Curry's (GSW) back, dislodging him from his rebounding position.
During the inbound, Thompson (GSW) and Jackson Jr. (MEM) mutually engage and disengage and the contact is marginal.
Adams (MEM) and Porter Jr. (GSW) mutually engage and marginal contact occurs as neither attempts to disengage during the driving shot attempt.
Wiggins (GSW) maintains a legal guarding position during the driving shot attempt by Brooks (MEM).
Brooks (MEM) commits a take foul on Curry (GSW).
Green (GSW) legally contests and cleanly blocks Jackson Jr.'s (MEM) jump shot attempt.
Jackson Jr. (MEM) commits a take foul on Curry (GSW).
Thompson (GSW) legally contests Jackson Jr.'s (MEM) jump shot attempt. Jackson Jr. extends his leg behind him during his release to initiate the marginal contact.
During the rebound, Porter Jr. (GSW) and Adams (MEM) mutually engage and disengage and the contact is marginal.

Adams (MEM) reaches for the loose ball and marginal contact occurs with Wiggins' (GSW) arm/head, which does not affect his ability to secure the rebound.  Contact to an opponent's head/face can be deemed marginal when the result of a natural basketball move, provided the contact is not disproportionate or uncontrolled.
Adams (MEM) commits a take foul on Wiggins (GSW).
